The paper discusses the development of better digital storage devices, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of natural mediums like DNA, bacteria, and protein for information storage also involves computational biology (cs.CE) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper specifically discusses DNA-based information storage, which falls under the category of bioinformatics (cs.BIO).
